<li><a href="/wiki/Extraordinary_rendition" title="Extraordinary rendition" class="mw-redirect">Extraordinary rendition</a> involves flying terror suspects abroad to countries where it is likely that they will be <a href="/wiki/Torture" title="Torture">tortured</a>. This is done to avoid the illegality of ordering their torture or carrying it out on US soil. By having another government order it, the intention to torture the suspect can be plausibly denied.</li>
